//!
//! # Zero Mutex
//!
//! Per `docs/ZERO-MUTEX.md` Tier 3 (program-with-mailbox): the
//! service IS the mailbox. Its registry lives on the worker thread;
//! mutation happens only inside the loop body; no lock primitive is
//! needed because no other thread reaches in. The handle exposes
//! `register`/`unregister` over a crossbeam channel — atomics +
//! `OnceLock` + `Arc` are the only shared-state primitives. Zero
